num_tested_probands: A single 31-year-old man was reported in the case study, who underwent genetic testing.
The report discusses a single 31-year-old patient observed in the clinic in 2018.
num_positive_het_probands: The proband was found to have biallelic variants in WARS2, not heterozygous variants.
There is no mention of probands being heterozygous for a pathogenic variant. The focus is on a single individual with described clinical presentations.
positive_phenotypes: The proband presented with a severe hyperkinetic movement disorder, dystonia, chorea, ballism, and developmental and cognitive delay.
The clinical presentation of the patient includes severe hyperkinetic movement disorder with uncontrollable dystonic and ballistic movements.
num_compound_or_double_hets: The proband was identified with two variants in WARS2, inherited from each parent, indicative of compound heterozygosity.
There is no mention of compound or double heterozygotes in the report.
